"What Difference Does It Make?" is a 1984 single by British band The Smiths. The single version can be found on the band's self-titled debut album The Smiths. A different version recorded for the John Peel Show on BBC Radio One is featured on the compilation album Hatful of Hollow. Morrissey has stated on more than one occasion that "What Difference Does It Make?" is among his least-favourite Smiths songs. However, it became one of the band's first significant chart hits, peaking at #12 in the UK.
